Maiharaji Altine, Gusau THE Zamfara State Government has selected 8,692 youths for it’s Social Investment Programme, who would to be given N10,000 each per month and be trained in their chosen career. Each of the coordinators and supervisors of the programme would receive N50,000 monthly. Governor Bello Matawalle said the beneficiaries would be spread to the various sectors of the state economy where they would gain more experience so that they could become employers of labour. He said, “The scheme will ensure that every youth in the state is fully engaged.” Copyright PUNCH.
